# Architecture Documentation - Whop Central Hub API

This document details the data flows, state logic, and component hierarchy of the Central Hub API to preserve AI context across coding sessions.

---

## Directory Structure & Concerns

```
├── prisma/
│   └── schema.prisma        # Database models (User, WhopApp, Customer, Transaction)
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── actions/         # Server Actions (settings, leaderboard logic)
│   │   ├── api/
│   │   │   ├── auth/        # OAuth redirect and callback routes
│   │   │   └── hub/         # Incoming sync endpoints (/notion-sync)
│   │   ├── dashboard/       # Hub user interface
│   │   ├── docs/            # Developer onboarding pages
│   │   ├── page.tsx         # Product landing page
│   │   └── layout.tsx       # Root layout
│   └── lib/
│       ├── analytics.tsx    # Bookkeeping & tax calculations
│       ├── db.ts            # Prisma client instance
│       └── encryption.ts    # AES-256-GCM encryption utilities
```

---

## Key Core Data Flows

### 1. Developer OAuth Flow
1. Developer visits `/` and clicks **Connect Account**.
2. Redirects to `/api/auth/whop` which starts the OAuth 2.1 PKCE authorization flow.
3. Upon approval, Whop redirects to `/api/auth/callback/whop`.
4. The callback handler exchanges the code for access/refresh tokens, encrypts the credentials, upserts the developer profile in the SQL database, sets a HTTP-only session cookie, and redirects to `/dashboard`.

### 2. Multi-App Activity Synchronization
```
[Whop Mini App] -> (POST /api/hub/notion-sync) -> [Central Hub API] -> [Decrypted Notion CRM API]
```
1. A Whop Mini App triggers a server mutation/action emitting a user activation.
2. It sends a `POST` request containing user headers (App ID, Email, Name, Tier, Niche).
3. The Central Hub `/api/hub/notion-sync` receives the payload, looks up the app owner's user account, decrypts their private Notion API keys, and forwards the record to their isolated Notion database page.

